title: Back to the grind after festive holiday break
text:
Back to the grind after festive holiday break 
PETALING JAYA: Itâ€™s back to the grind for many Malaysians who start work today after the Chinese New Year break, so parts of the North-South Expressway (NSE) were congested as they flocked home. 
PLUS Malaysia Bhd, operator of the NSE, said on Twitter that there was heavy traffic from Bidor heading towards Sungkai and Slim River in Perak at 6.45pm yesterday. 
In another tweet at about 7pm, PLUS noted that traffic was also congested from Simpang Renggam heading towards Sedenak and Kulai in Johor. 
A motorcycle accident at the 301.7km mark from Bangi to Kajang also caused a crawl of up to 5km. 
However, PLUS said traffic was mostly smooth along the Elite Highway and the New Klang Valley Expressway yesterday evening. 
Real-time traffic updates can be found via PLUS mobile apps, PLUSTrafik Twitter, PLUSLine and major radio stations.
